WEBVTT

00:07.485 --> 00:11.565
<i>♪ If I knew you were comin'</i>
<i>I'd have baked a cake ♪</i>

00:11.805 --> 00:14.205
<i>♪ Baked a cake, baked a cake ♪</i>

00:14.285 --> 00:17.045
<i>♪ If I knew you were comin'</i>
<i>I'd have baked a cake ♪</i>

00:17.125 --> 00:19.485
<i>♪ How'd you do?</i>
<i>How'd you do, how'd you do? ♪</i>

00:19.885 --> 00:23.125
<i>♪ Had you dropped me a letter</i>
<i>I'd have hired a band ♪</i>

00:23.205 --> 00:25.685
<i>♪ Grandest band in the land ♪</i>

00:25.765 --> 00:28.525
<i>♪ Had you dropped me a letter</i>
<i>I'd have hired a band ♪</i>

00:28.605 --> 00:31.165
<i>♪ And spread the welcome mat for you ♪</i>

00:31.245 --> 00:34.085
<i>♪ Oh, I don't know where you came from ♪</i>

00:34.165 --> 00:36.725
<i>♪ 'Cause I don't know where you've been ♪</i>

00:36.805 --> 00:39.845
<i>♪ But it really doesn't matter</i>
<i>Grab a chair and fill your platter ♪</i>

00:39.925 --> 00:42.405
<i>♪ And dig, dig, dig right in ♪</i>

00:42.765 --> 00:45.885
<i>♪ If I knew you were comin'</i>
<i>I'd have baked a cake ♪</i>

00:46.005 --> 00:48.405
<i>♪ Hired a band, goodness' sake! ♪</i>

00:48.485 --> 00:51.445
<i>-♪ If I knew you were comin' ♪</i>
<i>-</i>Not you! Piss off!

00:51.525 --> 00:53.205
<i>♪ How'd you do? How'd you do?  ♪</i>

00:53.285 --> 00:54.565
[man] What the fu--

00:59.645 --> 01:00.485
Lizzie?

01:08.405 --> 01:11.285
<i>♪ If I knew you were comin'</i>
<i>I'd have baked a cake ♪</i>

01:11.845 --> 01:13.965
<i>♪ Hired a band, goodness' sake! ♪</i>

01:14.045 --> 01:16.845
<i>♪ If I knew you were comin'</i>
<i>I'd have baked a cake ♪</i>

01:16.925 --> 01:19.005
<i>♪ How'd you do?</i>
<i>How'd you do, how'd you do? ♪</i>

01:19.085 --> 01:21.925
<i>♪ How'd you do, how'd you do?</i>
<i>How'd you do? ♪</i>

01:22.125 --> 01:24.525
<i>♪ How'd you do? ♪</i>

01:33.045 --> 01:34.365
-Hey.
-Hey.

01:35.085 --> 01:36.085
How are you?

01:36.765 --> 01:38.485
I'm fine. Why?

01:38.565 --> 01:40.485
What do you mean, why?
I’m asking how you are.

01:40.565 --> 01:43.405
-That's not weird, that's normal.
-You've never asked me how I am before.

01:43.485 --> 01:45.725
Bloody hell! I won't do it again, then.
Sorry for asking.

01:46.125 --> 01:47.085
That's more like it.

01:51.685 --> 01:54.405
Aww. Don't you want to live
happily ever after?

01:54.845 --> 01:57.365
Please. Do I look like
I have a Cinderella complex?

01:58.885 --> 01:59.885
Are you going?

01:59.965 --> 02:03.045
It's an appropriated American tradition
that celebrates sexism

02:03.125 --> 02:06.205
and peddles an unrealistic portrayal
of romantic love. So, no.

02:06.285 --> 02:08.925
Agreed. Ritualized teenage fun sucks.

02:11.565 --> 02:15.405
[sighs] Eric would have forced me to go.
He loves that stuff.

02:15.925 --> 02:19.485
-He genuinely has a Cinderella complex.
-Have you apologized yet?

02:20.285 --> 02:23.485
Yeah, I tried,
but he's still not talking to me.

02:23.565 --> 02:25.725
He'll come round. Maybe.

02:27.685 --> 02:30.725
Anyway, your 8:30 awaits.

02:34.885 --> 02:36.645
-Thanks. See you later.
-Good luck.

02:36.725 --> 02:37.685
See you later.

02:42.845 --> 02:46.605
[Liam] I don't understand why Lizzie
doesn’t want to go to the ball with me.

02:47.045 --> 02:49.925
I have tried every romantic gesture
in the book.

02:50.445 --> 02:51.805
Have you tried asking her?

02:53.405 --> 02:55.045
That was the first thing I did.

02:55.245 --> 02:58.805
She said that she was flattered,
but she wasn't dating.

02:59.845 --> 03:01.885
-Okay.
-But things change, though.

03:02.245 --> 03:03.405
And she was flattered.

03:03.485 --> 03:07.085
Well, I know it’s hard, but if you've
asked her and she's said no,

03:07.165 --> 03:09.365
then I think you've got your answer.

03:09.765 --> 03:13.285
But maybe her dad squished
the message on the cake with his foot,

03:13.645 --> 03:15.405
so she doesn't know
that I’m still interested?

03:15.485 --> 03:17.085
You said you sent her a letter,

03:18.405 --> 03:22.125
Yeah, it was full of glitter
and green Jelly Babies.

03:22.205 --> 03:23.325
I know that she likes them.

03:24.205 --> 03:26.725
[Liam] But the post is unreliable.
It might not have arrived.

03:26.805 --> 03:30.805
And you also spelt out "I love you"
on her lawn in leaves?

03:30.885 --> 03:33.645
-Yeah, but that could have blown away.
-I think the answer's no, Liam.

03:33.725 --> 03:35.765
But she hasn't actually said no.

03:35.845 --> 03:37.605
And girls love big gestures, right?

03:37.685 --> 03:40.645
Like Jackson singing to Maeve Wiley,
and now they're together.

03:40.885 --> 03:43.885
That's different.
Maeve actually likes Jackson.

03:45.645 --> 03:46.925
It would have been inappropriate

03:47.005 --> 03:49.005
if Jackson had continued
to make grand gestures

03:49.085 --> 03:52.565
to a girl who made it clear
she wasn't interested.

03:53.365 --> 03:54.925
Do you understand, Liam?

03:55.605 --> 03:56.605
No means no.

03:58.165 --> 03:59.645
Unless it means yes.

04:01.485 --> 04:05.885
Okay, let's.... um...
let's go through this again.

04:08.565 --> 04:10.565
[electronic pop music plays]

04:12.845 --> 04:14.845
[indistinct chatter]

04:16.325 --> 04:18.765
Hey! What time
shall I pick you up tonight?

04:19.965 --> 04:21.245
-What for?
-For the ball.

04:21.685 --> 04:23.085
I’m not going to the ball.

04:24.205 --> 04:25.645
Course you are. We're going together.

04:26.085 --> 04:28.085
What about me says school dance?

04:28.165 --> 04:30.525
-[chuckles] But...
-[scoffs]

04:31.085 --> 04:33.445
I bought a suit,
I got you a corsage.

04:33.565 --> 04:35.685
You got me a flower handcuff,
but forgot to invite me?

04:36.125 --> 04:39.205
Yeah... We're going out.

04:39.925 --> 04:41.085
I thought it was a given.

04:41.805 --> 04:44.605
Oh, come on. I've been
really looking forward to this.

04:44.685 --> 04:49.365
-Mm-hmm?
-Me and you, dancin', havin' fun?

04:50.885 --> 04:52.125
You know what fun is, right?

04:52.205 --> 04:54.445
-It's what people our age do sometimes--
-Yeah, very funny.

04:54.525 --> 04:56.045
Come on, it won't be good without you.

04:57.085 --> 04:58.405
Come on, please?

04:59.885 --> 05:01.125
-Fine.
-Yes!

05:01.205 --> 05:04.005
No selfies, or slow dances,
or soppy song requests.

05:04.085 --> 05:04.925
Okay, yeah, cool.

05:06.165 --> 05:07.685
-I'll pick you up at 7:30.
-Mm.

05:08.605 --> 05:12.285
-Wait, you do have a dress, right?
-Yeah, course. I'm not a troglodyte.

05:12.365 --> 05:14.165
-Yeah!
-[chuckles]

05:17.765 --> 05:18.685
Shit...

05:44.845 --> 05:45.685
[sighs]

05:46.965 --> 05:47.845
Ah...

05:47.925 --> 05:49.445
[ringing tone]

05:53.485 --> 05:54.525
[Jakob] <i>Yeah.</i>

05:54.685 --> 05:57.125
-Hello, Jakob.
-<i>Yeah, hello.</i>

05:57.205 --> 05:59.445
I seem to have broken my kitchen tap.

05:59.765 --> 06:01.685
-Who is this?
<i>-Jean.</i>

06:03.285 --> 06:05.925
Jean Milburn?
You did my bathroom recently.

06:06.005 --> 06:06.885
Yeah. I remember.

06:08.405 --> 06:10.805
Do you think you could possibly
come and fix it?

06:10.885 --> 06:12.565
<i>No, I can't. I'm busy.</i>

06:12.645 --> 06:15.565
Er... Okay. Well, it's not an emergency.

06:16.965 --> 06:18.005
Tomorrow?

06:18.165 --> 06:20.445
Well, I'll check my schedule
and get back to you.

06:20.525 --> 06:21.685
<i>Goodbye.</i>

06:26.645 --> 06:29.405
Sorry. Work stuff.

06:31.765 --> 06:33.285
And, uh... [clears throat]

06:33.405 --> 06:36.805
why do you think Moordale
would be a good fit for you, young lady?

06:36.885 --> 06:38.165
To be honest,

06:38.285 --> 06:40.525
my current school is in administration

06:40.605 --> 06:43.605
because the headmistress
embezzled our finances.

06:43.685 --> 06:47.365
She's on the run now in Mexico
with our geography substitute, Mr Peabody.

06:47.445 --> 06:51.685
So, I kind of need a new school.
For, like, education.

06:54.125 --> 06:55.445
-[sighs]
-It's true!

06:55.565 --> 06:58.485
Well... [clears throat]
honesty is exactly the kind of attribute

06:58.565 --> 07:00.645
we look for in this institution.

07:01.725 --> 07:07.845
Also, your grades are very impressive,
and we are aiming to improve our average.

07:07.925 --> 07:08.885
[clears throat]

07:15.765 --> 07:16.645
Come on.

07:23.765 --> 07:25.885
Ola? What are you doing here?

07:26.165 --> 07:30.605
Uh... I'm looking for a new school.
Your headmaster is considering me.

07:30.685 --> 07:32.285
Although he's a very rigid man.

07:32.365 --> 07:34.805
Like a living Easter Island statue.

07:34.885 --> 07:36.965
-[chuckles] Yeah.
-Stop flirting now. Come on.

07:37.045 --> 07:39.325
Just wait in the van.
I'll be there in a minute.

07:39.405 --> 07:42.125
[speaking Swedish]

07:42.205 --> 07:43.205
[sighs]

07:44.605 --> 07:47.085
[sighs] You never called.

07:47.685 --> 07:48.805
Yeah, I, um...

07:49.445 --> 07:52.245
I composed a bunch of texts,
and after reading them,

07:52.325 --> 07:54.125
I just felt immensely uncool.

07:54.205 --> 07:57.005
So, I decided to not text you anything.

07:58.165 --> 07:59.605
I'm an idiot, sorry.

07:59.685 --> 08:01.965
I heard the Untouchables
are coming in a limousine!

08:02.045 --> 08:05.765
Oh, my God! If I had a limousine, I would
totally have sex in it and film it.

08:06.205 --> 08:08.205
-[chuckles]
-School dance tonight.

08:08.285 --> 08:09.765
Right. Are you going?

08:10.805 --> 08:13.845
It’s an appropriated American tradition
that celebrates sexism

08:13.925 --> 08:16.285
and peddles an unrealistic portrayal
of romantic love, so--

08:16.365 --> 08:17.205
I like dances.

08:18.245 --> 08:19.085
You do?

08:19.165 --> 08:21.445
Yeah, I think dancing's fun.

08:22.685 --> 08:23.725
[chuckles]

08:24.485 --> 08:27.245
Anyway, I'd better go. Bye, Otis.

08:28.285 --> 08:29.325
See you.

08:33.445 --> 08:35.245
Ola! [clears throat]

08:35.325 --> 08:36.405
Ola, uh...

08:36.765 --> 08:39.445
Do you... do you want
to go to the dance with me?

08:40.245 --> 08:41.725
-Yes.
-Yeah.

08:41.805 --> 08:43.805
-Yeah.
-Okay, cool. [chuckles]

08:43.885 --> 08:46.005
Well,  um, it starts at eight, I think.

08:46.085 --> 08:48.085
So, aim to get there for seven?

08:48.165 --> 08:50.165
I'll pick you up at 6:30. On time's late.

08:50.245 --> 08:52.365
-I'll meet you at yours at seven.
-Okay.

08:52.445 --> 08:53.285
Okay.

08:55.925 --> 08:56.965
[sighs]

09:08.165 --> 09:09.245
[door closes]

09:10.085 --> 09:11.205
[bike brakes squeal]

09:17.725 --> 09:18.845
[scoffs]

09:20.285 --> 09:21.565
[Eric's mum] Eric!

09:22.565 --> 09:24.925
-You forgot the shopping list.
-[Eric] Oh, Mum.

09:25.965 --> 09:28.045
-[Eric's mum] I called Headmaster Groff.
-[Eric groans]

09:28.125 --> 09:31.245
He said that you can go
to the dance tonight if you want to.

09:31.325 --> 09:34.565
-[Eric] I don't.
-Maybe you can come to church with us?

09:34.645 --> 09:36.965
I don't go to church anymore, Mum.

09:37.885 --> 09:38.765
Hm?

09:39.605 --> 09:40.925
[sighs]

09:41.725 --> 09:43.805
Everyone loves you.

09:59.765 --> 10:01.205
[sighs]

10:01.685 --> 10:02.805
So, how's it lookin'?

10:04.365 --> 10:05.925
Well, you look like an angry aubergine.

10:06.405 --> 10:08.565
Yeah, well I can’t afford it anyway, so...

10:09.445 --> 10:10.845
Can't Action Man buy you a dress?

10:10.925 --> 10:13.565
His name is Jackson.
And, no, I'm not his housewife.

10:15.525 --> 10:17.005
Why does he annoy you so much?

10:17.085 --> 10:18.845
He doesn't. I actually quite like him.

10:19.285 --> 10:21.765
I'm just not sure
he's the right guy for you, that's all.

10:24.765 --> 10:27.725
Try this one. It's a little bit less
magician's assistant.

10:29.485 --> 10:31.085
I'm happy with Jackson, all right?

10:31.165 --> 10:34.125
Well, fine. Have a lovely life
watching Sergeant Do-Good swim

10:34.205 --> 10:36.645
while you raise an army
of his perfect children.

10:36.805 --> 10:37.845
Whatever.

10:42.845 --> 10:43.925
[chuckles]

10:44.125 --> 10:46.325
-[Sean] Well?
-Yeah, it’s actually nice.

10:51.525 --> 10:54.205
I told you my price limit.
This is way too expensive.

10:59.885 --> 11:00.765
Sean?

11:06.725 --> 11:08.125
[PA chimes]

11:08.205 --> 11:14.645
[Sean on PA] <i>Hello. I am so sorry</i>
<i>for interrupting your shopping today,</i>

11:14.725 --> 11:20.765
<i>but my little sister, Maeve, is going</i>
<i>to her first school dance tonight</i>

11:20.845 --> 11:24.965
<i>and she has just found the perfect dress.</i>

11:26.325 --> 11:28.605
<i>There she is! Come on out, Maeve. Come on.</i>

11:30.445 --> 11:32.045
<i>Doesn’t she look so pretty?</i>

11:33.005 --> 11:35.605
<i>Except, the problem is,</i>
<i>we can't afford this dress,</i>

11:36.405 --> 11:37.805
<i>because, recently...</i>

11:39.805 --> 11:40.965
<i>we were orphaned.</i>

11:41.725 --> 11:46.445
<i>Earlier this year, our dad,</i>
<i>who served this country bravely,</i>

11:46.965 --> 11:52.285
<i>died in combat and</i>
<i>our mum passed shortly after.</i>

11:53.925 --> 11:55.085
[whispers] <i>Cancer.</i>

11:55.725 --> 11:59.885
<i>But if they had been here today</i>
<i>to see my little sister,</i>

11:59.965 --> 12:04.885
<i>they would have been so proud</i>
<i>of their little girl.</i>

12:07.405 --> 12:11.925
<i>Now, I know it's unorthodox,</i>
<i>but if you could give anything,</i>

12:13.005 --> 12:18.325
<i>then we might be able to help my sister</i>
<i>get the dress of her dreams.</i>

12:19.365 --> 12:20.285
<i>Thank you.</i>

12:25.245 --> 12:27.965
What is your problem?
You can't say we're orphans!

12:28.485 --> 12:30.525
Oh, I'm sorry.
Would you rather I told them

12:30.605 --> 12:33.245
that Mum's a junkie
and that Dad fucked off?

12:33.525 --> 12:36.005
I don't think they would have enjoyed
that story as much.

12:36.485 --> 12:39.405
We were born alone
and we will die alone

12:39.485 --> 12:42.165
so we might as well get
what we can along the way.

12:44.165 --> 12:45.005
You're welcome.

12:53.205 --> 12:55.205
[Gospel music blaring on car radio]

12:58.525 --> 12:59.685
[engine revving]

13:04.445 --> 13:07.005
[man]<i></i>Hey, man,
do you know how to get to Ellencot?

13:07.085 --> 13:10.885
I’m trying to get to get to a wedding
reception and my GPS totally screwed me.

13:10.965 --> 13:12.125
Um...

13:12.205 --> 13:13.445
Yeah. Uh--

13:17.885 --> 13:21.205
Yeah... Yeah, you--
You're going in the right direction.

13:21.285 --> 13:24.445
Um, it's that way,
uh, it's about 15 minutes.

13:24.525 --> 13:26.245
Take a left at the primary school.

13:26.805 --> 13:29.245
-Okay. Thanks, man.
-Uh...

13:29.685 --> 13:32.045
Your nails are fierce.

13:32.605 --> 13:33.765
Thanks, kid.

13:35.125 --> 13:38.805
Want my advice? Stick to the jewel tones.

13:39.165 --> 13:40.685
[laughs]

13:40.765 --> 13:42.205
[revs engine]

13:43.325 --> 13:45.325
[music blares]

13:50.165 --> 13:52.325
<i>♪ Heard the angels sing ♪</i>

13:52.405 --> 13:54.045
<i>♪ Heard the angels moan ♪</i>

13:54.645 --> 13:57.405
<i>♪ Doo, doo-doo-doo-doo ♪</i>

13:58.405 --> 14:00.405
<i>-♪ I heard 'em moan ♪</i>
<i>-♪ I heard 'em moan ♪</i>

14:00.565 --> 14:02.485
<i>-♪ I heard 'em moan ♪</i>
<i>-♪ I heard 'em moan ♪</i>

14:02.685 --> 14:04.685
<i>-♪ I heard 'em moan ♪</i>
<i>-♪ I heard 'em moan ♪</i>

14:04.765 --> 14:06.965
<i>-♪ I heard 'em moan</i> ♪
<i>-♪ I heard 'em moan ♪</i>

14:07.045 --> 14:09.165
<i>-♪ Can I get a witness?</i>
<i>-♪ I heard 'em moan ♪</i>

14:09.245 --> 14:10.805
-[doorbell rings]
-<i>♪ I heard 'em moan ♪</i>

14:10.885 --> 14:11.845
I'll get it, Mum!

14:12.405 --> 14:13.885
<i>-♪ I heard 'em moan ♪</i>
-I'll get it!

14:14.645 --> 14:16.925
-Darling, is that for you?
-Yeah.

14:17.965 --> 14:19.965
-Where are you going?
-School dance.

14:24.805 --> 14:25.725
With who?

14:27.445 --> 14:30.845
Hey! Um... Wow. Okay... You look cool.

14:30.925 --> 14:34.445
-You look fantastic.
-Thank you. You look great yourself.

14:34.645 --> 14:35.485
Thanks.

14:36.045 --> 14:38.045
I'm here for the sink.

14:38.125 --> 14:40.925
-Great. Marvelous.
-[Jakob] Okay.

14:41.085 --> 14:43.405
-[Jean] Yeah.
-You behave.

14:44.325 --> 14:45.285
<i>You </i>behave.

14:48.885 --> 14:50.405
Do you want to come in for a bit?

14:50.485 --> 14:52.325
-No, we're good. See you.
-Okay.

14:52.405 --> 14:54.605
-Bye.
-Bye, have a lovely time.

14:54.685 --> 14:56.285
-Mum, actually...
-Yeah?

14:56.365 --> 14:59.925
Uh, do you think maybe
you could not sleep with Ola's dad?

15:00.005 --> 15:01.685
It's gonna make things
super awkward for me.

15:01.805 --> 15:04.405
I would never. Don't be silly. Um...

15:04.885 --> 15:06.685
Completely inappropriate.

15:07.085 --> 15:08.485
-Okay.
-Have a lovely time.

15:12.165 --> 15:14.965
Aww! You both look so smart.

15:16.205 --> 15:18.005
Okay, a little closer together now.

15:21.005 --> 15:21.965
[clears throat]

15:22.805 --> 15:23.645
Closer!

15:26.805 --> 15:28.285
Put your arm round him, love.

15:29.685 --> 15:31.205
Go on. Give him a proper hug!

15:32.045 --> 15:33.165
Just take the photo!

15:34.565 --> 15:35.645
Hold on.

15:37.525 --> 15:39.805
Christ!
Just take the bloody photo, Maureen.

15:42.125 --> 15:44.125
[70's funk music plays]

15:51.085 --> 15:52.565
-Lies!
-Rubbish!

15:52.645 --> 15:54.405
[laughter]

15:54.485 --> 15:56.925
-Ooh!
-Someone's looking groovy!

15:57.005 --> 15:58.005
-Mum!
-[laughs]

15:58.085 --> 16:00.925
Groovy is not a thing.
It hasn't been for a long time.

16:01.005 --> 16:02.805
-[chuckling]
-Come here.

16:03.205 --> 16:04.445
Have a brilliant time.

16:04.925 --> 16:05.885
Thank you.

16:05.965 --> 16:06.925
[Jackson] Mwah!

16:07.005 --> 16:08.165
-You look great.
-Thanks.

16:08.245 --> 16:10.725
-See you soon.
-Remember to be back at 10:30, yes?

16:10.805 --> 16:13.845
-What? Why?
-You've got training tomorrow morning.

16:14.165 --> 16:16.525
Yeah, but I thought
I could, you know... take tomorrow off.

16:16.965 --> 16:19.405
-Why would you think that?
-Because of the dance.

16:19.645 --> 16:21.525
I'm sure he can take tomorrow off.

16:21.605 --> 16:23.325
No, he can't.

16:24.045 --> 16:27.325
Can't I just have one fun night?
I never do this kind of thing.

16:27.405 --> 16:31.965
Look, you will thank me in a few years.
See you at 10:30. Go on. Have a good time.

16:35.765 --> 16:37.085
[sighs]

16:41.925 --> 16:43.445
